Section 1:
1 L.D. 1638
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 LABOR
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 646, L.D. 1638, “An Act Regarding
10 Disability Retirement Benefits Under the Maine Public Employees Retirement System”
11 Amend the bill in section 5 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 27 in L.D.) by inserting after
12 the following: "to" the following: 'January 1, 2024 for'
13 Amend the bill in section 5 in subsection 1 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 33 in L.D.) by
14 striking out the following: "should" and inserting the following: 'would'
15 Amend the bill in section 5 by striking out all of the last paragraph (page 1, lines 36 to
16 39 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
17 'The person must be paid the difference with interest accruing from January 1, 2024 to
18 the date the payment is made pursuant to this section. The rate of interest must be 6.5%.'
19 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
20 number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment makes the following changes to the bill.
23 1. It changes the retroactivity date to January 1, 2024 for a person who was receiving
24 disability retirement benefits under the Maine Public Employees Retirement System as of
25 December 31, 2024 if those retirement benefits were reduced because the person received
26 disability retirement benefits under the United States Social Security Act.
27 2. It requires that a person must be paid the difference between the amount of disability
28 retirement benefits, including any cost-of-living adjustments, the person would have
29 received absent any reduction of such benefits due to the receipt of disability retirement
30 benefits under the United States Social Security Act and the amount of disability retirement
31 benefits the person actually received.
Page 1 - 132LR1228(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 646, L.D. 1638
1 3. It provides that a person must be paid the difference with interest accruing from
2 January 1, 2024 to the date that the payment is made. It changes the rate of interest to 6.5%.
33 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
44 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1228(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
